This is a commond-line based client.
In the commond-line, type "make" to compile the client;
type "./client (username) (server IP) (server port)" to start.
This client support all the function required.
Username cannot be duplicated or you will be declined.
If you've already connected to server, you can know who are online and chat with them by typing.
Also, you will be decliend if the server has reached its limit of number of clients.
You will automatically send IDLE if you do nothing within 10 second.
You can shutdown your client client by type #exit or you can just press ctrl+c or just close your client window.
